The paper discusses a new scalable data analysis package powered by a Big Data management system, which extends the data scientists' familiar DataFrame operations to efficiently operate on managed data at scale. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the database (cs.DB) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the implementation of AFrame as a layer on top of Apache AsterixDB, which is a distributed system, indicating that the paper may also belong to the distributed computing (cs.DC) and data structures (cs.DS) sub-categories. Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of AFrame using a micro-benchmark, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category.
